FBIS4-56908 "drlat091_b_94011" FBIS-LAT-94-091 Daily Report 9 May 1994 Aruba Haiti Aristide Unable To Request Military Intervention Aristide Unable To Request Military Intervention FL1005192794 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1600 GMT 9 May 94 FL1005192794 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole French BFN [Text] On 7 May in another interview on CNN, Haitian President-in-Exile Jean-Bertrand Aristide said that in case the new sanctions against Haiti fail, the United States should overthrow the military. It is a question of political will, he said, nevertheless refusing to speak clearly of military intervention. He noted: Under the Constitution, if I ask for a military intervention, I will be dismissed.
